    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "In order to simulate the behaviour of real neurons, we will use recurrent neural networks. You will investigate the dynamic response of a linear recurrent network.  The network is inactive until is stimulated by a sustained input.  The response to this input `reverberates' through the network's recurrent connections until a steady-state activity is reached.  You will visualize and compute this dynamic response in different ways.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Linear recurrent network\n",
        "\n",
        "Consider a linear recurrent network with $N=20$ nodes (neurons), indexed by $k\\in\\left\\{1, \\ldots , N\\right\\}$.  Node activity is time-varying vector $\\textbf{v}(t)$, with $\\textbf{v}(0)=0$, meaning the network is inactive at the beginning.  Recurrent connectivity between nodes is a matrix $\\textbf{M}$ (size $N\\times N$).  The response to a sustained input vector $\\textbf{h}$ is determined by linear dynamic equation\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{d \\textbf{v}(t)}{dt} = - \\textbf{v}(t) + \\textbf{h} + \\textbf{M} \\cdot \\textbf{v}(t), \\qquad\\qquad \\textbf{v}(0) = 0  \n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Obtain matrix $\\textbf{M}$ from the provided function `ConnectionMatrix()`. This matrix is illustrated below. Note that the function also supplies two principal eigenvectors and eigenvalues of the matrix.\n",
        "\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "<div align=center>\n",
        "<img width=500 src=\"https://drive.google.com/uc?id=11hhFPVbxa10fHmzKrGrixSmInkUARlwO\"/>\n",
        "</div>\n",
        "\n",
        "\\\\\n",
        "Formally, the *exact* steady-state activity pattern follows from\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "0 = -\\textbf{v}_{ss} + \\textbf{h} + \\textbf{M} \\cdot \\textbf{v}_{ss}\\qquad\\Rightarrow\\qquad (\\textbf{I} - \\textbf{M}) \\cdot \\textbf{v}_{ss} = \\textbf{h} \\qquad\\Rightarrow\\qquad \\textbf{v}_{ss} =  (\\textbf{I} - \\textbf{M})^{-1} \\cdot \\textbf{h}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where $\\textbf{I}$ is the identity matrix.  Solve for $\\textbf{v}_{ss}^\\mathit{exact}$ with the Numpy `np.linalg.solve(A, B)`.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "In the lecture, the *approximate* steady-state solution was derived from the two principal eigenvectors:\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\textbf{v}_{ss}^\\mathit{approx} \\approx \\frac{\\textbf{h} \\cdot \\textbf{e}_1 }{1 -\\lambda_1} \\, \\textbf{e}_1 + \\frac{\\textbf{h} \\cdot \\textbf{e}_2 }{1 -\\lambda_2} \\, \\textbf{e}_2\n",
        "$$"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "IlU26Dkj9y1P"
      }
