        "Simulate the time-evolution of the system for several input vectors $\\textbf{h}_i$ (one at a time)!  \n",
        "\n",
        "Set the initial activity $\\textbf{v}_0 = 0$ to zero, and iteratively compute subsequent activity vectors $\\textbf{v}_i$.  To this end, proceed from time $0$ to time $20$ in steps of $\\Delta t=0.5$. For each step $i$, compute the current equilibrium vector (given the current activity, input, and connectivity)\n",
